Package com.github.mibac138.argparser.binder

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BindMethod  
    Binding
    Binding is a connector between Parser's output, interface SyntaxLinker's linking and interface BoundMethod's invoke
    BoundMethod
    Represents a bound method. Can be easily invoked using invoke
    Name
    Annotation used by some binders in order to automagically generate syntax
    ReusableSyntaxLinker  
    SyntaxGenerator
    Used by interface BoundMethods to generate syntax.
    SyntaxLinker
    Created by mibac138 on 19-06-2017.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnnotationBasedSyntaxGenerator<T extends Annotation>
    A little convenience class. Does the param checking for you
    Binder
    Common entry point for binding methods. You can initialize methods directly but it's recommended to use these methods when you can
    BindingImpl
    Default interface Binding implementation.
    CallableBoundMethod
    Kotlin's reflection based bound method (works for Java too*)
    JavaDefaultValueSyntaxGenerator
    Basically a port of Kotlin's optional KParameters. When setting default values parsers should return them if they couldn't parse the input
    KotlinDefaultValueSyntaxGenerator
    Generates relevant syntax for optional KParameters
    MethodBinder
    Created by mibac138 on 10-05-2017.
    NameSyntaxGenerator
    Generates relevant syntax using interface Name annotation
    NullSyntaxGenerator
    Represents an empty interface SyntaxGenerator
    ParamNameSyntaxGenerator
    Generates syntax based on KParameter's name. Works as a last resort option (generates syntax (NameComponent) only if it hasn't been already generated)
    SyntaxGeneratorManager
    Syntax generator consisting of other generators. Does nothing on it's own. When running generate it invokes all of the added generators.
    SyntaxLinkerImpl
    Created by mibac138 on 23-06-2017.
